Both required outputs are in place.

**`transcript.json`** — 25 iterations, 40 hypotheses, 40 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`. Top-level fields set (`dataset_id=ds001_aml`, `model_id=claude-opus-4-7`, `harness_id=claude-code-bundle@manual`, `max_iterations=25`).

**`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative walking through the iteration sequence: top clinical predictors (feature_057, feature_011, feature_006, feature_035, feature_099, with feature_063/feature_092 attenuating in adjustment), interaction tests (mostly null), sociodemographic findings (small but adjustment-robust race signal; no insurance main effect), and an overall ranked summary. Notably flags two prespecified hypotheses where the data refuted the original framing — h11.1 (the race disparity does NOT attenuate under clinical adjustment) and h25.2 (joint race+insurance after adjustment is marginally significant, p=0.027).
